This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring September 12, 2010, as National Grandparents Day. The proclamation acknowledges the important role that grandparents play in American families and communities, passing down stories and traditions through generations. It highlights the milestones witnessed by grandparents and the love, care, and understanding they provide. The proclamation also recognizes the hard work and sacrifice of previous generations, which have enabled the rights and opportunities accessible to all Americans today. The article encourages Americans to show appreciation and respect for their grandparents and those in their community.